</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
</p></div>
<p > PSH will hold these Public Shares in Treasury. The net asset value per Public Share related to this buyback is 77.06 USD / 57.55 GBP which was calculated as of 14 July 2026. After giving effect to the above buyback, PSH has 173,717,025 Public Shares outstanding. Excluded from the shares outstanding are 37,239,725 Public Shares held in Treasury. The prices per Public Share were calculated by Jefferies.  </p>
<p > The one special voting share (held by PS Holdings Independent Voting Company Limited) has not been affected.  </p>
<p > <b>About Pershing Square Holdings, Ltd. <br /></b>Pershing Square Holdings, Ltd. (LN:PSH) (LN:PSHD) is an investment holding company structured as a closed-ended fund.  </p>
<p > Category: (PSH:ShareRepurchases)  </p>
<p > <b>Media Contact <br /></b><b>Camarco <br /></b>Ed Gascoigne-Pees / Julia Tilley +44 (0)20 3781 8339, <a rel="nofollow" href="mailto:mediainquiries@pershingsquareholdings.com" shape="rect" target="_blank">mediainquiries@pershingsquareholdings.com</a>  </p>
<p ><span class="bwct31415"></span></p>
